tourBios.exmtStatus: Finished T9 at 2015 Web.com Tour Qualifying Tournament
tourBios.carHigh: Played on the Gateway Tour (2004-06), Golden Bear Tour (1999-2003) and the eGolf Tour (2007). Also played on Hooters Tour and D.P. Tour. 2012: Made the cut in 10 of 24 events and was inside the top 20 six times. His best finish came at the Neediest Kids Championship (T8)...Fired a second-round 65 at the Cox Classic. Posted all four rounds in the 60s to finish T13...Fired a 65 at The Rex Hospital Open and was tied for second after the first round. Went on to finish T16 in Raleigh. 2009: Missed the cut at the South Georgia Classic in his only start. 2008: Played his rookie season on the Web.com Tour. 2007: Turned in a final-round, 10-under 62, including a double eagle, eagle and five birdies, to advance on the number at the second stage of the PGA TOUR Qualifying Tournament. 2004: Missed the cut at The First Tee Arkansas Classic.
tourBios.otherCarHigh: Qualified for the 1996 U.S. Open at Oakland Hills CC but missed the cut...Two-time All-Southeastern Conference selection in his two years at Auburn (1997-98).
tourBios.personal: Attended Marist High School in Dunwoody, Ga...Biggest thrill outside golf is the birth of his children...Favorite college team is Auburn and pro team is the Atlanta Braves...Favorite TV show is "The O'Reilly Factor." Favorite musician is Johnny Cash...Enjoys Mexican food...Got his start in golf from his parents.

dyn.dynResults: His best finish on the Web.com Tour in 2016 is T25th at the Servientrega Championship Presented by Efecty.
